t-Evo-super-lightweight-road-bike-helmet_photo-by-Francesca-Caporali_white-angled-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/15105921/Limar-Ultralight-Evo-super-lightweight-road-bike-helmet_photo-by-Francesca-Caporali_white-angled-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-265425\">photo by Francesca Caporali</figcaption></figure><p>The new helmet also appears to eliminate the anti-insect mesh from the front vents, a feature many riders questioned for its divisive aesthetics &amp; necessity. The updated helmet also adds a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2017/11/01/limars-new-ultralight-lux-adds-features-but-remains-one-of-the-lightest-helmets-in-the-world/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">small LED blinkie light</a> over the dial adjuster at the rear. Adding just about 9g extra, you can always pop it off it you don’t want the added visibility.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/15105915/Limar-Ultralight-Evo-super-lightweight-road-bike-helmet_Iridescent-Blue-front-rear.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/15105915/Limar-Ultralight-Evo-super-lightweight-road-bike-helmet_Iridescent-Blue-front-rear.jpg\" alt=\"Limar Ultralight Evo super lightweight road bike helmet,&nbsp;front &amp; rear views\" width=\"1500\" height=\"600\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/15105915/Limar-Ultralight-Evo-super-lightweight-road-bike-helmet_Iridescent-Blue-front-rear.jpg 1500w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/15105915/Limar-Ultralight-Evo-super-lightweight-road-bike-helmet_Iridescent-Blue-front-rear-297x119.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/15105915/Limar-Ultralig