.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/15105915/Limar-Ultralight-Evo-super-lightweight-road-bike-helmet_Iridescent-Blue-front-rear-120x48.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/15105915/Limar-Ultralight-Evo-super-lightweight-road-bike-helmet_Iridescent-Blue-front-rear-768x307.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/15105915/Limar-Ultralight-Evo-super-lightweight-road-bike-helmet_Iridescent-Blue-front-rear-696x278.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/15105915/Limar-Ultralight-Evo-super-lightweight-road-bike-helmet_Iridescent-Blue-front-rear-1068x427.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/15105915/Limar-Ultralight-Evo-super-lightweight-road-bike-helmet_Iridescent-Blue-front-rear-1050x420.jpg 1050w\"></a></p><p>Other than that, the Ultralight Evo is functionally identical to the phased-out Ultralight+, including the exact same 22 air vents, internal air channeling, washable padding, and minimalist but very adjustable Competition+ dial &amp; webbing fit adjustment.</p><h3>Limar Ultralight Evo – Pricing, options, weight &amp; availability</h3><figure id=\"attachment_265423\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-265423\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/15105909/Limar-Ultralight-Evo-super-lightweight-road-bike-helmet_photo-by-Valentina-Celeste_handlebar.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/15105909/Limar-Ultralight-Evo-super-lightweight-road-bike-helmet_photo-by-Valentina-Celeste_handlebar.jpg\" alt=\"Limar Ultralight Evo super lightweight road bike helmet,&nbsp;handlebar\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\